                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" id="allergy_sng_1" hclass="sense" fkcefr="b2"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a medical condition that causes you to react badly or feel ill when you eat or touch a particular substance</span></span><ul class="examples" htag="ul" hclass="examples"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">He has a severe nut allergy.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x"><span class="cl">Food allergies</span> affect six to eight per cent of children.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"> <span class="cf" htag="span" hclass="cf">allergy to something</span> <span class="x">I have an allergy to animal hair.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">Hay fever is caused by an allergy to pollen.</span></li></ul><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" unbox="extra_examples" id="allergy_unbox_1"><span class="box_title">Extra Examples</span><ul class="examples" hclass="examples" htag="ul"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="unx">Hair and feathers can cause allergies.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="unx">He developed an allergy to wheat.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="unx">In severe cases your doctor may recommend allergy shots.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="unx">You may wish to consult a food allergy specialist for help in planning your diet.</span></li></ul></span></div><span class="topic-g"><span class="prefix">Topics </span><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/health-problems?level=b2" title="Topic health-problems"><span class="topic" href="l2:health:health_problems?cefr=b2"><span class="topic_name">Health problems</span><span class="topic_cefr">b2</span></span></a></span><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" unbox="snippet" id="allergy_unbox_2"><span class="box_title"